Part 1: Technical Requirements Document (TRD)
1. Project Overview
Project Name: Navro Capital

Client: Girish Bagrecha

Mission: A premium, high-trust portfolio site for a specialist broker handling Bonds, Unlisted Stocks, and Mutual Funds.

Primary Goal: Lead generation via WhatsApp, Form, and Call scheduling.

2. Branding & UI/UX
Theme: Bright/Light Mode only. Use a "Wealth Management" palette: White background, Deep Navy Blue or Emerald Green accents, and professional slate greys.

Vibe: Minimalist, fast-loading, and authoritative.

Interactions: All phone numbers and emails must be "Click to Copy" or "Click to Call/Mail."

3. Core Pages & Features
Home Page:

Hero section with "Smart Wealth Management" & "Investment Management" messaging.

Dynamic Market Insight: A text-only section on the home page.

Admin Access: A hidden or low-profile /admin route with hardcoded credentials to update the Market Insight text.

Bonds Page:

Filterable/Searchable table using data from Bonds.xlsx.

Columns: Issuance, Rating, Coupon, Indicative Yield, Maturity.

Stocks Page:

Focus on "Unlisted Equity Opportunities."

Display based on the provided image (e.g., NSE, HDB, Swiggy, etc.).

Mutual Funds Page: * Placeholder: "Coming Soon" with a "Notify Me" or "Inquire Now" button.


Legal/Disclaimers: * Static page containing the Master Disclaimer, Bond Disclaimer, and Mutual Fund Disclaimer.

4. Contact & Conversion
WhatsApp: Floating button or direct link to +91 9731038350.

Form: Simple lead gen (Name, Phone, Interest).

Meeting: Integrated Calendly or similar 30-min meeting scheduler link.

5. Technical Constraints
Stack: Pure HTML5, CSS3 (Tailwind recommended), and Vanilla JS.

Hosting: Netlify (Free Tier).

Data: No database. The Bonds and Stocks data will be stored as a data.json file within the repository for maximum speed.